  "name": "Split Shot",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You fragment a ranged spell into a pair of smaller shots. If your next action is to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} without a duration that requires an attack roll against a single target and has no effect beyond dealing damage, you roll a single attack roll and compare the result to the AC of two targets within the spell's range. The spell deals only half its usual damage to each target.</p>\n<p>This counts as one attack for your multiple attack penalty.</p>"
